725158f-b.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 14th Street
725158f-b.text:
27th Avenue, at the S.E. corner of 14th Street, showing St. Georges Protestant Episoopal Church. The house to the left of the church is the parish house, on 27th Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  View 1 June 2, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 2,3: March 13, 1927

725160f-a.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 14th Street
725160f-a.text:
14-22 27th Avenue, adjoining the S.E. corner of 14th Street, showing the rectory of St. Georges Protestant Eoiscopal Church. It appears from the 1873 and 1891 maps of Queens County that the rectory stood at the S.E. corner of 14th Street, where the brick churd is now located, and that the church itself, then a frame edifice, occupied the N.E. corner of Astoria Avenue, formorly Main Street, and 14th Street, where the Public Library now stands.
View 1: P. L. Sperr  March 13, 1931.
View 2: Federal Art Project -- W.P.A.  1337
Berenice Abbott
A45
